ALLEGHENY COUNTY , PA . , PLANS SPRING CHARTER VOTE . Allegheny County residents are expected to vote next Spring on proposed charter reforms , as public hearings begin this week on the proposal . The committee with the job of changing the county charter holds the first of five public hearings Thursday . Under the plan , the current Allegheny County Board of Commissioners would be dissolved in favor of an elected county executive and county council and an appointed manager . Committee members said there is too much work to do for the proposal to make it in time for the November election . - - U . S . Municipal Desk , 212 - 859 - 1650 
